definition.value: An organochlorine compound that is ethanol substituted by at least one chloro group.
Any organic heterobicyclic compound containing ortho-fused furan and pyridazine rings.
A tertiary ammonium ion that is the conjugate acid of pacritinib resulting from the protonation of the pyrrolidine nitrogen; Major species at pH 7.3.
The citrate salt of pacritinib.

A sulfone that is thiolane substituted by two oxo groups at position 1 and by a (chloroacetyl)(2,2-dimethylpropyl)amino group at position 3. It is a covalent inhibitor of Pin1 (Ki = 17 nM) that inhibits Myc-driven tumors in vivo.

N(1),N(11)-bis(ethyl)norspermine (DENSPM), a N-terminally alkylated tetraamine and polyamine mimetics, disrupts polyamine pool homeostasis by modulating the activities of the biosynthetic enzymes, ornithine decarboxylase (ODC), and S-adenosylmethionine decarboxylase (AdoMetDC).
A chloroalkene that is ethene in which one or more of the hydrogens has been replaced by chlorine.

A member of the class of pyrazolopyrimidines that is 4,5-dihydro-1H-pyrazolo[3,4-d]pyrimidine substituted by 2-chlorophenyl, oxo, and (2R)-3,3,3-trifluoro-2-methylpropyl groups at positions 1, 4 and 6, respectively. It is a potent and selective inhibitor of phosphodiesterase 9 (PDE9), currently in pre-clinical development for the treatment of Alzheimer's disease.
